comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-18T05:54:11.258Z",codex-sdk-vcs-20260718,"Implementation start 2026-07-18: dependencies pm-3mna and pm-cbwg are live-verified closed. This wide lane will build the package against public SDK exports only, exercise custom schema/statuses, commands/hooks, attributable history replay, and produce a structured gap report plus packed temp-workspace proof."
  "2026-07-18T07:17:34.514Z",codex-sdk-vcs-20260718,"Acceptance evidence 2026-07-18: @unbrained/pm-vcs ships 2 domain types, 4 fields, a custom commits_to ontology, VCS profile/workflow, 7 domain commands, reviewed-merge hook, point-in-time history reconstruction, and durable merge-ledger projection using public SDK contracts only. Linked tests pass 2/2. Packed manual proof installed the tarball into an isolated project, installed vcs, applied its profile, created/proposed/merged a changeset, reconstructed version 1, replayed version=1/processed=1 identically across fresh processes, passed isolated package doctor and tracker validation, and preserved normal core create/get."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-18T07:17:35.726Z",codex-sdk-vcs-20260718,"Gap disposition: production content-addressed object storage, tree diffing, and network transport are VCS-product concerns, not universal SDK gaps. Cross-item plus relationship atomic commit remains an explicit bounded-exemplar waiver; larger durable indexing and scale work stays on canonical pm-ju83/pm-m2il lineage."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-18T07:17:35.117Z",codex-sdk-vcs-20260718,"A foreign-domain package can remain core-independent when the host injects lifecycle, history, and relationship services. Runtime package imports stay type-only; values come from context.sdk, allowing bundled installed copies to execute without private paths or nested CLI resolution."
